<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:codified="http://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>38-112</num>
  <heading>Masculine pronoun to include both male and female.</heading>
  <text>Wherever the masculine pronoun occurs in this chapter it shall be construed to apply to either male or female teachers or employees of the Board of Education.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History">June 20, 1906, 34 Stat. 321, ch. 3446, § 12</annotation>
    <annotation doc="Pub. L. 90-292" type="History">Apr. 22, 1968, 82 Stat. 102, Pub. L. 90-292, § 3(d)</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 31-116.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 31-117.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
